Method Detail

checkChannelState

public abstract void checkChannelState()
                                throws RemoteException
Check that the channel is in the desired state, called in the constructor and by external controllers after they might have changed the state. Note: If this function throws a RemoteException or AntCommandFailedException in the constructor, the constructor will log it and throw a ClosedChannelException.

Throws:
RemoteException - If the channel is dead. If you detect an unrecoverable state, kill your channel, then throw this.
